snippet: With Republicans often sharply split on big issues like spending and taxes, Democratic votes have been decisive in getting major legislation through the House.
abstract: Democratic votes have been decisive in getting major legislation through Republican-controlled House; Democrats control 200 seats, handful more than they had in last Congress, and Republicans are often sharply split on big issues like spending and taxes.

byline.contributor: Derek Willis contributed reporting from Washington.

lead_paragraph: With Republicans often sharply split on big issues like spending and taxes, Democratic votes have been decisive in getting major legislation through the House.

headline.seo: House Democrats Have More Power in New Congress
headline.main: For Democrats in G.O.P.-Led House, a New Congress Means Some New Muscle
headline.print_headline: For Democrats in G.O.P.-Led House, a New Congress Means Some New Muscle
